<br>
The whole point was then summed up in what Jesus said to him:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;Becaue you have seen Me, have you believed? Blessed are they who did not see, and yet believed.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Jesus was showing that while He did show Himself to Thomas, one of the 12, it wasn't going to happen to everyone. But they would be blessed because they believed without &quot;seeing&quot; it.<br>
<br>
I know people today, that are saying &quot;I want God to show up in my living room and tell me&quot;.. they wouldn't change. They'd put it off on a vision or dream. Those that are truly listening to God will &quot;get&quot; it without having seen Jesus. We will all see Him one day. The question will be, HOW will He see us, as His family, or His foe? <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:fuchsia;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:x-small;">....·´¨¨))</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:small;">-:¦:-</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:teal;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:x-small;"> <br>
