<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Many a good man has spent his entire life trying to live down a past indiscretion.  The Apostle Thomas certainly fits into that category.<br>
<br>
Throughout the ages, his name has become synonymous with doubt and a weakness of faith because of his initial refusal to accept Christ's Resurrection.  Still, the writings of early Church History paint a very different picture of him.  His labors for the Lord have taken on legendary proportions.<br>
<br>
The Apostle Thomas was a native of Galilee and a fisherman by trade.  In the Gospels, he is referred to also as &quot;Didymus,&quot;<br>
meaning <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;twin&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> .  However, there is no specific reference anywhere concerning a sibling of this type.  When the Apostles embarked upon their great mission to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;...go, and teach all nations,&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  it was Thomas who journeyed the farthest from Jerusalem.  It was his lot to carry Christ's message eastward, with India as his ultimate destination.<br>
<br>
Although India was a pagan and barbaric land, Thomas had great success in winning converts to Christianity.  The newly established Church there was noted for the exemplary moral and ascetic lives that their members zealously embraced.  The Apostle even converted the family members of several Indian princes.  This, however, would eventually bring about the demise of Thomas.  A certain Prince Misdaeus, whose wife and son had been baptized by Thomas, arranged a meeting with the Apostle.  When Thomas came to the designated site, he was murdered by five soldiers.  Tradition tells us that his sacred remains were taken to Mesopotamia for burial.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heartjoys>heartjoys</A> at: 10/8/03 1:47 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#B87333>- </font><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth>Sparrow's Hearth</a><font color=#B87333> - </font><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7>Theology/Bible Study</a> <font color=#B87333> - </font><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth"><font face=verdana size=4>Sparrow's Hearth</font></a><font color=#B87333> - </font> <h1 align=center><a href=http://bible.gospelcom.net/><img src=http://heartjoys.fcpages.com/Sparrow'sHearth/logo_gospelcom.gif></a></h1><p>
